  "body": "We currently don't recursively fetch for missing blocks voted by attestation. e.g.  Receive attestation A with for block B.  The node doesn't have block B, so the node fetches it. The block has parent C, node doesn't have that so it fetches block C. This is one of the reason sometime we see forks can't be resolved with prysm nodes",
